
A:
	I can't believe you threw that ball over the fence. Now you're going to have to go into that dark, scary, spooky forest all by yourself!

B:
	I don't know if I can go alone. Will you go with me?

A:
	And live with my stepmother?

B:
	Your stepmother lives in that dark, scary, spooky forest?

A:
	Hurry up! You're making me worried. [hears scream] What was that? Hold on!

B:
	Oh no! Where did you go?

A:
	[speaking together] { No no. Clear out man, can't you; and
                               don't be a fool.

B:
	I think I found the ball, but my jeans are stuck on the fence! Help!

A:
	It hurts so much, make it stop!

B:
	We're going to die!

A:
	We're not all going to die in six months.

B:
	In six months? What about right now?

A:
	Be quiet. 

B:
	(whispers) Did you hear something?

A:
	Who is it?

B:
	I don't know. I thought it was you that heard something.
